Link Multiball sticks a ball behind the target due to machine malfunction. Can be wiggles out without tilting.

location_machine_xrefs.condition: I’ve had a Batman pinball machine in my bar & played it daily for months. This machine has a cool green LED on the backglass, but otherwise played completely different than version I’m used to. I think I’m part due to the almost flat setup (like a 1960s machine) that has been employed in this model. The factory set high scores are astronomically unobtainable - maybe if you played the best three games of your life back-to-back-to-back. I heard that they host tournaments at this location, & had driven 61 miles to see what locals had achieved in this game for comparison. Oh, well - played two games & left three credits for the kiddies.
